HELLO

I decided to make V2 out of my previous map, because it had alot of bugs and things that bothered me, so I fixed alot of stuff to made it work better.
Added more into it, so this wouldn't be just fix of the map, but other version.

NEW
Hidden bar room. Lots of secret areas. Easier to go through chimney (No more crouching needed).
Smoother car drop. Fixed textures on walls and retextured boxes. Added more realism look for the house. And so on... See for yourself, hope you like it. :D

SPAWN POINTS
Terrorists - Spawn at the mountains. 
Counter terrorists - Spawn from the main building.

OBJECTIVE
The basic idea is for the terrorists to plant the bomb on "sauna" area (A) on the map and completely ruin the nice vacation OR just kill everybody and take over.
Counter terrorists have to protect the sauna from demolition by all cost!

INFO
This map has lots of new secret places all over the map, by mastering em, you have an advantage, such as invisible bridge, invisible walls, breakable walls etc...
Based on 8-8 matches, but holds 40 players limit, if you don't have any friends to play with, (or it's just me) don't you worry this map is bot friendly.

Happy Gaming!

A non-cluttered (I get 150fps on max res/settings DX9) port of the classic DM3 map from Quake 1. Not changed much, only added some slight detail here and there, and broke through a wall for balancing purposes (three ways to bombsites instead of just two).

I made this map a loooong time ago, for personal use, but since nobody ported any q1 maps, I thought I'd at least release this one. Also, I already know about all the mapping errors (it was made a long time ago) and illogical lighting (I tried to "explain" the lighting with skylights, but I might've missed some).

Anyway, I hope there's a Q1 fan like me out there who'll appreciate this.

_sText:
Hi! I present to you my new map "De_Quadroshock" for "Counter-Strike: Source" (-bomb/defuse mission).
I worked much on this map and hope for you will be exciting to play. -)
I am game developer, but in such way I accumulate experience in level-design and keep fit.
The map is made from scratch and have original concept and design.
Also here are totally destroyable columns. And walls with physicalized destroyable bricks, which can be thrown down.
Plus only for this map I made something like a holographic panorama of an invented secret city (-Hi for City-17, from HL2 ! :) ).

Background story:
An attempt to attack was committed on the underground bunker of a secret military-scientific complex. The government is deeply shocked by this unexpected attack on such a secret complex. Nobody knows how the terrorists came in there. But the first attack was stopped!
Now the second wave of attack is expected, much hotter.
It is supposed that the purpose of the terrorists is to destroy with bombs two points in the bunker :
1. The structural column at point A – above it is located the biological weapons lab.
2. The power generators at point B. Also above is the floor with the chemical weapons lab.
The bunker itself is made up of 4 main parts with an additional central block where a supercomputer is located.
Attention! The supercomputer in the central block was already damaged in the first attack. Avoid electrical discharges from supercomputer.
You can also use the ventilation system for suddenly attack.
And use hot traps – explosive barrels with dangerous objects around them – fry the ass of your virtual opponents!
Powerful weapons and crafty tactics will make you cool and dangerous.
Have a good hunting! :)

This map is currently on the GB-UK 40 man public server, swing by there and get it voted on if you want to play it online! The map is set around some pyramids in ruin/desert type scenario. It includes bridges, water, underground passages, sniper positions and of course, double doors!

This is a complete rebuild of de_pyramid_css everything was built from the ground up to be optimised to work on large servers. updates to the map are: displacements - no longer is the sand flat and boring. the whole map has been given bumpy ground to look more realistic and add depth. more detail - the tall boring walls that block off the outside world are gone and replaced with detailed buildings to add more variety to the map. optimised - I rebuilt every building to take advantage of all the techniques the source engine has to lower the frame rate for large amounts of players.
